37109>>>>>    
37109>>>>>    Function IsLoggedIn Returns Boolean
37111>>>>>        String sLoginName
37111>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession bLoggedIn
37111>>>>>        
37111>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37112>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37114>>>>>            Forward Get IsLoggedIn to bLoggedIn
37116>>>>>            Function_Return bLoggedIn
37117>>>>>        End
37117>>>>>>
37117>>>>>        
37117>>>>>        Get psLoginName to sLoginName
37118>>>>>        
37118>>>>>        Function_Return (sLoginName <> "")
37119>>>>>    End_Function
37120>>>>>    
37120>>>>>    
37120>>>>>    //
37120>>>>>    // This procedure is called when validating a session and after logging in. Its purpose is to 
37120>>>>>    // update properties based on the session and user data. Augment this function to update 
37120>>>>>    // properties based on the session / user table. Note that WebAppUser and WebAppSession contain
37120>>>>>    // the right records when this procedure is called.
37120>>>>>    //
37120>>>>>    // Params:
37120>>>>>    //      bClear   True if the procedure is called before session validation to clear properties.
37120>>>>>    //
37120>>>>>    Procedure UpdateSessionProperties Boolean bClear
37122>>>>>        Handle hoUserDD
37122>>>>>        
37122>>>>>        Get phoUserDD to hoUserDD
37123>>>>>        
37123>>>>>        //  Update user properties
37123>>>>>        If (not(bClear) and HasRecord(hoUserDD)) Begin
37125>>>>>            Set psUsername to (Trim(WebAppUser.FullName))
37126>>>>>            Set psLoginName to (Trim(WebAppUser.LoginName))
37127>>>>>            Set piUserRights to WebAppUser.Rights
37128>>>>>            
37128>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesSet 
37129>>>>>        End
37129>>>>>>
37129>>>>>        Else Begin
37130>>>>>            Set psUsername to ""
37131>>>>>            Set psLoginName to ""
37132>>>>>            Set piUserRights to 0
37133>>>>>            
37133>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesClear
37134>>>>>        End
37134>>>>>>
37134>>>>>    End_Procedure
37135>>>>>    
37135>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesSet
37137>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37137>>>>>    End_Procedure
37138>>>>>    
37138>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesClear
37140>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37140>>>>>    End_Procedure
37141>>>>>    
37141>>>>>    Procedure EndSession
37143>>>>>        Integer iErr
37143>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession
37143>>>>>        Handle hoSessionDD       
37143>>>>>        
37143>>>>>        Get phoSessionDD to hoSessionDD
37144>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37145>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37147>>>>>            Forward Send EndSession
37149>>>>>            Procedure_Return
37150>>>>>        End
37150>>>>>>
37150>>>>>            
37150>>>>>        //  Check if session exists
37150>>>>>        Send Clear of hoSessionDD
37151>>>>>        Get psSessionKey to WebAppSession.SessionKey
37152>>>>>        
37152>>>>>        Send Find of hoSessionDD EQ Index.1
37153>>>>>        If (Found) Begin
37155>>>>>            Set Field_Changed_Value of hoSessionDD Field WebAppSession.Active to "N"
37156>>>>>            Get Request_Validate of hoSessionDD to iErr
37157>>>>>            If (iErr) Begin
37159>>>>>                // this should not happen. If it does its a programming error
37159>>>>>                Error DFERR_PROGRAM C_$WebAppSessionValidateFailed
37160>>>>>>
37160>>>>>                Procedure_Return
37161>>>>>            End
37161>>>>>>
37161>>>>>            Send Request_Save of hoSessionDD
37162>>>>>        End
37162>>>>>>
37162>>>>>    End_Procedure
37163>>>>>
37163>>>>>End_Class
