37513>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37513>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37513>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37516>>>
37516>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37516>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37516>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37516>>>        Case Begin
37516>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37518>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37518>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37518>>>                Case Break
37519>>>                
37519>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37522>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37522>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37522>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37522>>>                Case Break
37523>>>                
37523>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37526>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37526>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37526>>>                Case Break
37527>>>                
37527>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37527>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37527>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37527>>>                  
37527>>>        Case End
37527>>>
37527>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37527>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37527>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37528>>>
37528>>>    End_Procedure
37529>>>
37529>>>End_Object
